# "+" shortcut (extended for this repo)

When the user sends "+" as a standalone message, do ALL of the following, in order:

1. Verify current branch is `main` (`git checkout main` if needed).
2. Commit all changes with a sensible message and push to `origin main`.
3. Build and deploy the iOS app: run `npm run ios`.
   - If an iPhone is reachable (cable or Wi-Fi pairing), this installs and
     launches the app on it.
   - If no phone is reachable, the script still builds the app and exits
     successfully — tell the user (in Estonian) that the app was built but not
     installed, and that they should plug in / wake the phone and send "+"
     again (or just ask) to install.
4. Report briefly in Estonian what was pushed and whether the app reached the
   phone.

If the iOS build fails, still complete the push, then diagnose and fix the
build. Never leave the working tree uncommitted after a "+".
